<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419619>
    dc:description "Fig. 40. Ophiactis cf. brachygenys H.L. Clark, 1911 (IDSSE EEB-SW0015 = heptamerous specimen). A. Dorsal disc. B. Ventral disc (first and second ventral arm plates highlighted). C. Lateral disc. D. Radial shields. E–F. Oral frame (operculiform lateral oral papillae highlighted). G. Dorsal arm. H. Ventral arm. Abbreviations: as = adoral shield; dap = dorsal arm plate; gs = genital slit; os = oral shield; rs = radial shield; tp = tentacle pore; ts = tentacle scale; vap = ventral arm plate. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C–E, G–H = 500 µm; F = 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419619/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419621>
    dc:description "Fig. 41. Ophiactis cf. brachygenys H.L. Clark, 1911, SEM (IDSSE EEB-SW0015 = heptamerous specimen). A–C. Lateral arm plate (internal, external). D–H. Vertebrae. D. Proximal view. E. Distal view. F. Ventral view. G. Dorsal view. H. Lateral view. Abbreviations: D = dorsal; Dist = distal; dl = dorsal lobe; mo = muscle opening; no = nerve opening; Prox = proximal; V = ventral; vl = ventral lobe. Scale bars = 300 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419621/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419623>
    dc:description "Fig. 42. Ophiactis cf. brachygenys H.L. Clark, 1911 (IDSSE EEB-SW0016 = hexamerous specimen). A. Dorsal disc. B. Ventral disc. C. Radial shields. D. Lateral disc. E. Disc spine. F. Oral frame. G. Dorsal arm. H. Ventral arm. Abbreviations: as = adoral shield; dap = dorsal arm plate; ds = disc spine; gs = genital slit; os = oral shield; rs = radial shield; tp = tentacle pore; ts = tentacle scale; vap = ventral arm plate. Scale bars: A–B = 500 µm; C–H = 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419623/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419625>
    dc:description "Fig. 43. Family Asteronychidae Ljungman, 1867, Maximum likelihood (ML) trees based on partial 16S and COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). A. 16S ML. B. COI ML. Abbreviations: ECS = East China Sea; JP = Japan; SC = Sub-Clade; SCS = South China Sea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419625/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419627>
    dc:description "Fig. 44. Families Euryalidae Gray, 1840 and Gorgonocephalidae Ljungman, 1867, Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on partial COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). Abbreviations: AN = Antarctica; IC = Inter-Clade; NZ = New Zealand; RI = Reunion Island; SC = Sub-Clade; SCS = South China Sea; SO = Sothern Ocean." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419627/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419629>
    dc:description "Fig. 45. Family Ophiomusaidae O’Hara et al., 2018, Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on partial COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). Abbreviations: NZ = New Zealand; SC = Sub-Clade; SCS = South China Sea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419629/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419631>
    dc:description "Fig. 46. Family Ophiotomidae Paterson, 1985, Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on partial COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). Abbreviations: IC = Inter Clade; SC = Sub-Clade; SCS = South China Sea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419631/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419633>
    dc:description "Fig. 47. Family Ophiacanthidae Ljungman, 1867, Maximum likelihood (ML) trees based on partial 16S and COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). A. 16S ML. B. COI ML. Abbreviations: C = Clade; IC = Inter-Clade; NZ = New Zealand; SC = Sub Clade; SCS = South China Sea; TS = Tasman Sea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419633/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419635>
    dc:description "Fig. 48. Family Ophiactidae Matsumoto, 1915, Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on partial COI sequences (bootstrap support values were generated with rapid bootstrapping algorithm for 1000 replicates). Abbreviations: AUS = Australia; IC = Inter-Clade; NZ = New Zealand; PNG = Papua New Guinea; SC = Sub-Clade; SCS = South China Sea; TS = Tasman Sea." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6419635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

